<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-15T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/359: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-15T14:00:00-05:00">January 15, 1934—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6. Your 11, January 14, midnight, first paragraph. Legation in Guatemala
                            City has been instructed to communicate with President Ubico in the
                            sense suggested.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>